    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Rapid depletion of nutrients in your soil can indeed be a bit of a mystery, but it's not uncommon for certain factors to cause this. Overwatering, for instance, can lead to leaching, where nutrients are washed away from the soil. Similarly, if you're using a fast-release fertilizer, it might be providing a quick boost but also a quick drain on your soil's nutrient reserves. It's like a feast for your plants, but if they can't digest it properly, they might end up with a tummy ache. To prevent this, consider using slow-release fertilizers or organic matter like compost to feed your plants over a longer period. And always remember, a well-fed garden is a happy garden, but too much of a good thing can lead to a little bit of a problem. Keep an eye on your watering schedule and your fertilizer choices, and your tomato plants should be able to enjoy their feast without any issues.",
